Second Gentleman Douglas Emhoff will be visiting Krakow, Poland, and Berlin, Germany, to combat antisemitism and support Holocaust remembrance on behalf of the Biden-Harris Administration. In Krakow, he will visit the Memorial and Museum at Auschwitz-Birkenau, participate in a wreath-laying ceremony, and attend the annual commemoration of International Holocaust Remembrance Day. U.S. Special Envoy to Monitor and Combat Antisemitism, Ambassador Deborah Lipstadt, will also join the visit. In Berlin, Emhoff will attend a meeting of special envoys and coordinators working to combat antisemitism, along with Ambassador Lipstadt. Additionally, Emhoff will engage with local Jewish communities, civil society representatives, and visit historical and cultural sites in both cities.